      "text": "Take any \"fond\" smoking memory and run the full footage. The morning coffee-and-cigarette: yes, there was relief — because you'd been in withdrawal all night and the cigarette ended it. Now add the rest: the taste that actually made you cough, the stale smell on your fingers, the knowledge in the back of your mind that you'd rather not be doing it, the fact that a non-smoker enjoyed that same coffee more, for free, with no monster to feed. Suddenly the snapshot isn't romantic — it's a picture of a person scratching an itch they wish they didn't have.\n\nDo this a few times with your most cherished smoking images and something shifts permanently: the glow comes off. The memories stop being temptations and become accurate records of a trap. This is the same skill as the Day 8 \"trade the picture\" tool, but applied to the past rather than the present — and it closes off the last hiding place the addiction had."
